The key of the exports_objects.lines is changed (the trailing - has been

Also the lineno should be converted to string because a replace() gonna be

pull_commit_message:
Fix getting lineno of an exported object

The key of the exports_objects.lines is changed (the trailing - has been
removed). The trailing char should also be removed when we want to access to
it.
Also the lineno should be converted to string because a replace gonna be
called on it

pulltitle: bug fixes, #16 and handling of exports_objects.lines
pullsbody:
- #16: on windows, with CRLF fileendings, tag addresses end with
     \r, causing tag lookup to fail
     remove those '\r$' in regexify
  TODO: line ending variations should be handled properly when
        splitting the file into lines in the first place
- for some reason, tagVarRefsId may be called on IDENTIFIER nodes
  without fourth argument (why?), for instance when processing
  lib/jsctags/traits.js;
  guard handling of exports_objects.lines to keep jsctags from
  falling over
  TODO: check whether this hides a bug
- in getTags, exports_objects.lines needs to be addressed with
  tag name, without trailing '-', to avoid undefined lineno
pull_repo_desc: A set of static analysis tools for JavaScript
pull_commit_message:
bug fixes, #16 and exports_objects.lines

- #16: on windows, with CRLF fileendings, tag addresses end with
       \r, causing tag lookup to fail
       remove those '\r$' in regexify
  TODO: line ending variations should be handled properly when
        splitting the file into lines in the first place
- for some reason, tagVarRefsId may be called on IDENTIFIER nodes
  without fourth argument (why?), for instance when processing
  lib/jsctags/traits.js;
  guard handling of exports_objects.lines to keep jsctags from
  falling over
  TODO: check whether this hides a bug
- in getTags, exports_objects.lines needs to be addressed with
  tag name, without trailing '-', to avoid undefined lineno

pullsbody:
I wanted to fiddle with jsctags the other day, and I realized I could not install it straight away. The Makefile was too old, and David Herman [told me](https://twitter.com/#!/littlecalculist/status/101690772138635264) on Twitter that nobody really cared enough to fix it.

I cared.

---

This commit only impacts on the Makefile, which means it does not have side-effects on the rest of the project.

---

Please review it. There may be a more straightforward manner.
- Added `LIB_CFA2_SRC` since the position of cfa has moved away from `narcissus/`;
- Modified `LIB_NARCISSUS_SRC` since narcissus itself has moved away from `lib/`;
- Corrected `make uninstall` as well.
pull_repo_desc: A set of static analysis tools for JavaScript
pull_commit_message: Makefile updated to the current tree. jsctags lives

pullsbody:
I've implemented the `--sort` flag to mimic the one found in Exuberant Ctags:
- `--sort=no` sorts by line number (a little unintuitive, I know, but that's how ctags does it)
- `--sort=yes` sorts alphabetically on the tag names

Ctags has yet another option -- `foldcase` -- which I haven't implemented here.

I'm working on integrating jsctags with the taglist.vim plugin, and this flag will ease that process. It's a more elegant solution than doing the sorting in the plugin itself.

Do let me know if there's anything I should improve about the code. Thanks!
pull_repo_desc: A set of static analysis tools for JavaScript
pull_commit_message:
Add --sort option.

A value of 'no' sorts by line number, a value of 'yes' sorts
alphabetically.

pullsbody:
I've implemented the `--sort` flag to mimic the one found in Exuberant Ctags:
- `--sort=no` sorts by line number (a little unintuitive, I know, but that's how ctags does it)
- `--sort=yes` sorts alphabetically on the tag names

Ctags has yet another option -- `foldcase` -- which I haven't implemented here.

I'm working on integrating jsctags with the taglist.vim plugin, and this flag will ease that process. It's a more elegant solution than doing the sorting in the plugin itself.

Do let me know if there's anything I should improve about the code. Thanks!

pullsbody:
Hi,

I've added the ability for jsctags to print to stdout.

I've also added the `-f` tag as an alternative for the `-o` tag, in line with ctag's behavior.

Both changes will help integrate it with existing editor plugins that were built for ctags.

I sent this pull request to pcwalton's branch previously, but it seems to have disappeared.. seeing as there's an official mozilla branch now, I'm trying again. Hope to hear from you guys.

Regards,
Jez
